<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2536] topics tool should allow users to alter topic configuration</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2536</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we added dynamic config, we added a kafka-config tool (which can be used to maintain configs for non-topic entities), and remove the capability from kafka-topic tool.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Removing the capability from kafka-topic is:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Breaks backward compatibility in our most essential tools. This has significant impact on usability.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Kinda confusing that --create --config works but --alter --config does not. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest fixing this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
